Calculates the probability

Source: R/length.R
length_set.Rd

Given several probabilities it looks for how probable is to have a vector of each length

length_set(fuzziness)

Arguments

fuzziness

The probabilities

Value

A vector with the probability of each set

Examples

length_set(c(0.5, 0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.25, 0.23))
#>          0          1          2          3          4          5          6 
#> 0.09095625 0.28848750 0.34851875 0.20302500 0.06009375 0.00848750 0.00043125
